solution:
Assume the $n$ vacancies ("holes") in the O lattice are independent of the $n$ occupied interstitial positions. The occupied O positions are independent of the occupied X positions; therefore, the total number of occupancy configurations $W$, or degeneracy $g$, is the product of the degeneracies of vacancies in the O lattice and those of occupied positions in the X lattice. Each of these degeneracies is given by equation (1). Thus,

\begin{equation*}
W=g=\binom{N}{n}^{2} \tag{5}
\end{equation*}

Hence, the entropy $S$ of the crystal is

\begin{equation*}
S \approx 2 k n \ln \frac{N}{n} \tag{6}
\end{equation*}

The average kinetic energy density of the gas molecules is

\begin{equation*}  
u=\frac{3}{2} n k T  
\end{equation*}

